1
00:01:26,795 --> 00:01:30,340
[Big Jim grunting, laughing]

2
00:01:30,424 --> 00:01:31,425
Nice!

3
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:34,136
[breathes shakily]

4
00:01:38,015 --> 00:01:42,060
[Big Jim] My old man used to say
he wanted me to better myself.

5
00:01:42,144 --> 00:01:43,187
[kisses] I love you.

6
00:01:44,313 --> 00:01:47,191
[Big Jim]
But I could see in his eyes he didn't.

7
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:50,652
[raspberry, scoffs] "Better myself."

8
00:01:50,736 --> 00:01:52,446
[grunting]

9
00:01:52,529 --> 00:01:54,573
- No. [chuckles]
- I got you.

10
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:56,992
Nice, Jimmy. Way to get off the line.

11
00:01:57,075 --> 00:01:58,368
Attaboy!

12
00:01:59,328 --> 00:02:00,787
- [grunts]
- [Big Jim] Oh!

13
00:02:00,871 --> 00:02:02,706
- [Young Jimmy giggling]
- [Big Jim] Gremlin.

14
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,791
[Big Jim]
You know what they never tell you?

15
00:02:05,501 --> 00:02:11,590
They don't tell you
that the love of your life… could be your child.

16
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:18,347
Are you a threat to the mental health
of any of my patients?

17
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:21,642
[distorted] Are you a threat?
Are you a threat? Are you a threat?

18
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:24,561
[normal] Hi. Where are you heading off to?

19
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:27,564
[breathes shakily] Just gonna go home.

20
00:02:27,648 --> 00:02:29,149
You can't. You promised.

21
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:30,692
I never promised anything.

22
00:02:30,776 --> 00:02:31,777
You did.

23
00:02:33,737 --> 00:02:34,738
You did.

24
00:02:36,740 --> 00:02:38,033
You promised.

25
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:39,867
[Jessica gasps]

26
00:02:41,245 --> 00:02:42,245
[giggling]

27
00:02:44,081 --> 00:02:45,082
[Larry] Hey, James.

28
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,166
What?

29
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:51,672
[Big Jim] Whoa. Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

30
00:02:52,381 --> 00:02:53,382
[Larry] James.

31
00:02:53,465 --> 00:02:54,508
[grunting]

32
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:56,218
[exhales sharply]

33
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:59,012
- Hey, James.
- [laughing] James.

34
00:03:00,389 --> 00:03:01,390
[gasps]

35
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:04,101
[Larry chuckles]

36
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:09,690
You were having some dream.

37
00:03:12,943 --> 00:03:14,194
Did I say anything?

38
00:03:14,278 --> 00:03:19,700
No. But it did make me think
that my stories yesterday may have given you some nightmares.

39
00:03:24,872 --> 00:03:25,873
Stories?

40
00:03:29,084 --> 00:03:30,544
That's what they are.

41
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:33,046
Sometimes I do that.

42
00:03:34,506 --> 00:03:35,799
Lie to your friends?

43
00:03:37,259 --> 00:03:38,259
Huh?

44
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:40,387
What? No. No.

45
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:42,014
Well, you just said you lied to me.

46
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:57,905
So either you lie to your friends, or you lie to people who aren't your friends, which pretty much tells me where I stand either way.

47
00:03:58,989 --> 00:04:00,115
That's not it.

48
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:02,576
Okay.

49
00:04:04,703 --> 00:04:07,831
All right, um… All right, look, it's...

50
00:04:07,915 --> 00:04:11,251
Relax, Larry. I'm not surprised.

51
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:21,428
What are you... What are you saying?

52
00:04:23,055 --> 00:04:26,141
I guess if I'd given it more thought,
I would have realized you were lying.

53
00:04:26,225 --> 00:04:29,853
It's not lying. It's storytelling.
I'm not a liar. I'm a raconteur.

54
00:04:29,937 --> 00:04:31,855
[spits] Look, whatever.

55
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:34,733
Your details were off,
and God's in the details.

56
00:04:36,193 --> 00:04:37,945
[toothbrush scrubbing]

57
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:41,281
Okay. What "details?"

58
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:45,619
- You said you grew up digging graves.
- I did.

59
00:04:46,245 --> 00:04:49,498
Yet you didn't dig one for Jessica Roach.

60
00:04:53,627 --> 00:04:56,296
See?
That's how I know you're full of shit.

61
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:07,850
Then you would know
that you need to dig a grave in the right kind of soil.

62
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,226
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

63
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:11,812
And it's hard to find in the dark.

64
00:05:11,895 --> 00:05:13,021
Of course.

65
00:05:13,105 --> 00:05:17,484
And this man, he pulled up
on the road across from my van.

66
00:05:17,568 --> 00:05:19,820
Yeah, that guy. He keeps showing up.

67
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,910
I meant to go back.

68
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:28,871
I just didn't have the time to do it.

69
00:05:28,954 --> 00:05:32,165
Larry. It's okay.

70
00:05:35,586 --> 00:05:37,212
- It's not.
- It's fine.

71
00:05:37,296 --> 00:05:41,008
Everybody in here tells stories.
I tell everybody I played for OSU...

72
00:05:41,091 --> 00:05:42,134
It's not!

73
00:05:43,177 --> 00:05:44,761
[sighs]

74
00:05:45,637 --> 00:05:46,638
I...

75
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:51,268
Hmm. [chuckles]

76
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:56,190
I'm telling the truth.

77
00:05:57,983 --> 00:05:59,443
You just said it was a story.

78
00:06:00,027 --> 00:06:01,236
That was the lie.

79
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,487
Oh, that was?

80
00:06:02,571 --> 00:06:03,572
Yeah.

81
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:06,366
[stammers]

82
00:06:08,952 --> 00:06:13,040
I'm not lying, James.

83
00:06:21,215 --> 00:06:22,674
[breathes shakily]

84
00:06:23,926 --> 00:06:25,511
You're not a killer, man.

85
00:06:25,594 --> 00:06:27,012
[mouths words] I am.

86
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:29,848
I've looked into the eyes of a few.

87
00:06:32,518 --> 00:06:34,061
And you don't have those eyes.

88
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:42,611
What eyes do I have?

89
00:06:45,906 --> 00:06:46,907
A wannabe's.

90
00:06:53,497 --> 00:06:56,250
- Meet me in the woodshop later.
- Why?

91
00:06:58,710 --> 00:06:59,711
[scoffs]

92
00:07:00,254 --> 00:07:02,673
I wanna show you what kind of eyes I have.

93
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:06,426
[Holt] Chow, maggots.

94
00:07:24,695 --> 00:07:27,030
[chattering]

95
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:42,045
[guard] Shut the fuck up!

96
00:07:54,975 --> 00:07:56,018
[sighs]

97
00:08:00,981 --> 00:08:03,150
[panting]

98
00:08:14,369 --> 00:08:17,206
[grunting rapidly]

99
00:08:23,879 --> 00:08:25,589
You could always request PC.

100
00:08:25,672 --> 00:08:28,008
[radio chatter]

101
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:42,105
Might as well open up, Jim.

102
00:08:54,076 --> 00:08:55,160
Mind if I come in?

103
00:08:55,244 --> 00:08:56,954
I'd rather come out.

104
00:09:09,132 --> 00:09:10,342
Where's your girlfriend?

105
00:09:11,134 --> 00:09:13,220
Is he the one you're supposed to rat on?

106
00:09:15,222 --> 00:09:17,057
Cause I... I would support that.

107
00:09:20,018 --> 00:09:24,147
A kid killer? You kidding me, Jim?
I would have your back on that.

108
00:09:25,148 --> 00:09:27,401
- Yeah?
- I'd be your true blue, bud.

109
00:09:30,571 --> 00:09:31,738
What would it cost me?

110
00:09:32,656 --> 00:09:33,657
Nothing.

111
00:09:35,409 --> 00:09:36,410
Really.

112
00:09:37,035 --> 00:09:41,874
Some things are bigger than us and we can all agree that motherfucker has to get got.

113
00:09:42,374 --> 00:09:43,917
[inmate screaming]

114
00:09:44,001 --> 00:09:45,752
[inmate laughing]

115
00:09:48,338 --> 00:09:50,424
So who would we be working for?

116
00:09:55,095 --> 00:09:56,722
You mean who am I working for?

117
00:09:59,016 --> 00:10:03,228
Yes, but we'd be in this together.

118
00:10:03,312 --> 00:10:07,524
A-And maybe, if I did good,
it would be like an audition for me.

119
00:10:07,608 --> 00:10:09,610
And I can get a job with the Marshals.

120
00:10:12,321 --> 00:10:15,032
Well, if I was working for the Marshals,
maybe.

121
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:16,408
So who you working for?

122
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:18,911
[chuckles]

123
00:10:21,580 --> 00:10:23,415
I tell you what, Mr. Carter.

124
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:24,499
What?

125
00:10:26,210 --> 00:10:27,836
You call off the dogs for a week...

126
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:30,589
Ooh, uh. Why would I do that, Jim?

127
00:10:34,426 --> 00:10:36,678
- So I know you can.
- And you'll do what?

128
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:43,227
- Tell you who I'm working for.
- So, tell me.

129
00:10:43,894 --> 00:10:47,314
A week from now.
If I'm still walking upright.

130
00:10:47,397 --> 00:10:48,440
[Carter laughs]

131
00:10:49,525 --> 00:10:54,321
That's not... That's not… That's not how our relationship works, Jim.

132
00:10:54,404 --> 00:10:56,323
I don't think you can call anyone off.

133
00:10:56,406 --> 00:10:57,908
How you gonna call me off you?

134
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,998
Well, you fucked with my phone calls.

135
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:08,752
And you already put a snitch jacket on me.

136
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:14,258
What else you gonna do?

137
00:11:15,592 --> 00:11:17,469
- You don't wanna find that out.
- Yeah.

138
00:11:22,099 --> 00:11:23,141
I do.

139
00:11:26,854 --> 00:11:27,896
[chuckles]

140
00:11:29,106 --> 00:11:30,107
[chuckles]

141
00:11:31,066 --> 00:11:32,109
Okay then.

142
00:11:33,318 --> 00:11:34,444
Enjoy your day.

143
00:11:36,488 --> 00:11:37,531
Savor it.

144
00:11:45,247 --> 00:11:46,975
- [Big Jim] I was on the phone.
- [Sammy] Yep.

145
00:11:46,999 --> 00:11:51,378
- On hold for three fucking hours.
- [chuckles] Three hour... [stammers]

146
00:11:51,461 --> 00:11:55,507
I didn't even know that if it's...
If it's breakfast or-or lunch anymore.

147
00:11:55,591 --> 00:11:57,509
- It's... It's lunch.
- Ooh, ah.

148
00:11:58,010 --> 00:11:59,386
[sighs] And all-all...

149
00:12:00,304 --> 00:12:11,231
- Here you go.
- [stammers] All to tell me to call back tomorrow to talk... to talk to the one guy, the one guy who... who, uh, can let me know why Jimmy's funds were frozen.

150
00:12:11,315 --> 00:12:15,527
Well, you know,
maybe you could drive out there again and sit and stare at the prison.

151
00:12:15,611 --> 00:12:16,820
Come on. Stop.

152
00:12:16,904 --> 00:12:17,905
[chuckling]

153
00:12:17,988 --> 00:12:19,781
This is fucking serious.

154
00:12:19,865 --> 00:12:21,491
I know. Uh, what are you having?

155
00:12:21,992 --> 00:12:26,622
Uh… Ch... A churger.

156
00:12:27,831 --> 00:12:31,210
- What?
- [stammers] The cheeserburger.

157
00:12:31,293 --> 00:12:32,503
No, you said "churger."

158
00:12:34,046 --> 00:12:35,839
- I did?
- Yeah.

159
00:12:36,507 --> 00:12:38,592
Hi, folks.
Can I get you something to start?

160
00:12:38,675 --> 00:12:42,179
Oh, hi. Uh, yeah. I'll have ice tea.

161
00:12:42,262 --> 00:12:43,263
Hon?

162
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:48,894
Uh… A... A coff of cuppee, and-and-and-and a churger.

163
00:12:49,478 --> 00:12:52,523
Uh... Uh... The... The...
I don't know, the cheese... Ow. Fuck.

164
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:54,650
Call 911. He's having a stroke.

165
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:55,901
- Oh. Oh, God.
- What?

166
00:12:55,984 --> 00:12:57,611
- 911.
- [server] Okay.

167
00:12:57,694 --> 00:12:58,695
Okay.

168
00:12:58,779 --> 00:13:00,948
It's okay. It's okay. Okay. Okay. Okay.

169
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:04,993
- Oh, God.
- [coughing] [Sammy] 911!

170
00:13:11,834 --> 00:13:13,210
[Mr. Gigante clears throat]

171
00:13:33,939 --> 00:13:37,484
Good friend of mine
got the pancreatic cancer.

172
00:13:39,862 --> 00:13:41,947
Doctor said he'd be dead in four months.

173
00:13:44,491 --> 00:13:53,333
A week later he slipped walking up
some icy steps of a church, mind you, and hit his fucking head.

174
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:59,590
Died right there in front
of his wife, one of his kids.

175
00:14:02,843 --> 00:14:09,683
Know what his last words were before he bled out all over the steps of St. Augustine's?

176
00:14:12,936 --> 00:14:15,314
[breathes heavily]

177
00:14:20,027 --> 00:14:24,364
"You just… never fucking know."

178
00:14:36,627 --> 00:14:37,628
[kisses]

179
00:15:09,034 --> 00:15:11,286
[Larry sighs]

180
00:15:25,342 --> 00:15:26,468
[Larry chuckles]

181
00:15:53,912 --> 00:15:57,249
Oh, how'd you get in here?

182
00:15:58,792 --> 00:16:00,002
Door was open.

183
00:16:00,085 --> 00:16:01,086
Oh.

184
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:07,634
What you working on?

185
00:16:11,555 --> 00:16:12,556
[Larry sighs]

186
00:16:15,058 --> 00:16:16,435
[Larry] James.

187
00:16:16,518 --> 00:16:17,936
[sighs, chuckles]

188
00:16:20,522 --> 00:16:21,732
I finished them.

189
00:16:27,404 --> 00:16:30,324
Twenty-one? Why?

190
00:16:31,742 --> 00:16:34,119
Um, because I like to carve.

191
00:16:36,079 --> 00:16:39,041
No. Why 21?

192
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:42,336
Why not 20 or an even two dozen?

193
00:16:48,258 --> 00:16:49,259
[chuckles]

194
00:16:49,343 --> 00:16:51,720
Like, I carve well. See?

195
00:16:58,894 --> 00:17:01,063
It's too bad I don't paint well.
[chuckles]

196
00:17:02,523 --> 00:17:04,107
I'll leave that to Gary.

197
00:17:06,693 --> 00:17:08,319
Gary paints them black.

198
00:17:08,904 --> 00:17:10,948
Blacker than any black you've ever seen.

199
00:17:13,492 --> 00:17:14,701
Shipping these to Gary?

200
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:17,871
Home, yeah.

201
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,836
Do you know what they're for, James?

202
00:17:26,296 --> 00:17:27,339
No.

203
00:17:31,969 --> 00:17:33,303
They watch over the dead.

204
00:17:38,308 --> 00:17:42,688
They guard their spirits to make sure they're okay.

205
00:17:50,571 --> 00:17:52,573
These are the eyes you wanted me to see?

206
00:17:53,448 --> 00:17:55,158
Well, there's these too.

207
00:17:56,368 --> 00:17:58,453
[both chuckle]

208
00:17:59,496 --> 00:18:00,497
Right.

209
00:18:02,749 --> 00:18:04,209
You know, James.

210
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:12,718
You thinking that I was a liar, that made me sick to my stomach.

211
00:18:14,178 --> 00:18:17,806
Because then maybe you'd think
that I don't take what I do seriously.

212
00:18:18,807 --> 00:18:22,644
[smacks lips] There's a... a... a care
that should be taken.

213
00:18:23,145 --> 00:18:26,732
That's what I'm saying.
It shouldn't be casual.

214
00:18:27,357 --> 00:18:32,779
You know, not like your 80 women…
[chuckles] …you've been with.

215
00:18:32,863 --> 00:18:38,452
No. I'm sorry to say, but you probably don't remember some of their names.

216
00:18:40,454 --> 00:18:44,249
Maybe their body parts start to blur.

217
00:18:46,793 --> 00:18:47,920
Am I wrong?

218
00:18:51,256 --> 00:18:52,549
It was just sex, Larry.

219
00:18:52,633 --> 00:18:55,219
[chuckles] Oh, it's never just sex.

220
00:18:55,719 --> 00:18:57,137
Never just anything.

221
00:18:59,056 --> 00:19:02,226
[chuckles] Every interaction you have
with a person means something.

222
00:19:02,309 --> 00:19:07,356
We... We... That's what we owe to the… to the... the world.

223
00:19:07,439 --> 00:19:08,440
To history.

224
00:19:08,524 --> 00:19:10,526
Sometimes it's just sex.

225
00:19:10,609 --> 00:19:13,070
No. [chuckles]

226
00:19:14,112 --> 00:19:18,575
If every interaction
with another person had the same weight we'd all go insane, Larry.

227
00:19:20,702 --> 00:19:23,413
No. You fucking hear me?

228
00:19:23,497 --> 00:19:24,998
No, no, no, no, no.

229
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:27,876
Shut the fuck up and listen to me.

230
00:19:29,378 --> 00:19:30,879
We are part of something.

231
00:19:32,214 --> 00:19:36,093
I am a part of something.

232
00:19:37,427 --> 00:19:47,813
When I folded those clothes, that was an act of kindness from a... a… a deity. [chuckles]

233
00:19:50,148 --> 00:19:51,191
Whose clothes?

234
00:19:53,610 --> 00:19:54,903
Who are we talking about?

235
00:19:56,029 --> 00:19:57,114
[sighs]

236
00:19:59,366 --> 00:20:01,201
Tricia Reitler's.

237
00:20:03,203 --> 00:20:06,415
[inhales deeply]
Everyone was looking for her.

238
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:08,834
They still are.

239
00:20:10,544 --> 00:20:12,129
She got in your van too?

240
00:20:19,511 --> 00:20:20,804
She was a handful.

241
00:20:22,055 --> 00:20:23,640
She punched like a man.

242
00:20:24,224 --> 00:20:27,019
And I didn't wanna stab her, James.

243
00:20:27,102 --> 00:20:31,273
I didn't stab her…
because I was going to stab her.

244
00:20:31,356 --> 00:20:33,692
I stabbed her
to stop her from hitting me. Man.

245
00:20:35,944 --> 00:20:38,363
[scoffs, sighs]

246
00:20:38,447 --> 00:20:39,781
But that didn't work.

247
00:20:40,991 --> 00:20:43,076
She just kept on trying to hurt me.

248
00:20:45,329 --> 00:20:46,538
I had to choke her.

249
00:20:49,875 --> 00:20:51,460
You stabbed her and choked her?

250
00:20:51,543 --> 00:20:53,754
Such a nasty fucking girl.

251
00:20:53,837 --> 00:20:57,925
I must have passed out.
When I woke up, there she was lying there.

252
00:20:58,008 --> 00:20:59,134
Naked and all.

253
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,763
No pulse.

254
00:21:04,932 --> 00:21:15,150
But to your point, James. To your point… I did dig her grave.

255
00:21:16,193 --> 00:21:17,736
I know you made fun of me earlier.

256
00:21:17,819 --> 00:21:22,616
But I've dug hundreds of graves
since I was a child.

257
00:21:24,117 --> 00:21:27,579
Probably more than you've had women.
[chuckles]

