00:42:24,461 --> 00:42:26,421
What were you doing during all this?

507
00:42:26,505 --> 00:42:31,301
[Gary scoffs]
I was, like, in shock. You know?

508
00:42:31,927 --> 00:42:33,095
Mm-hmm.

509
00:42:33,178 --> 00:42:37,391
[Gary] And she's lying there afterwards, and I see this look Larry gets in his eyes.

510
00:42:37,891 --> 00:42:39,309
[Brian] What kind of look?

511
00:42:39,393 --> 00:42:40,686
Kind you never wanna see.

512
00:42:45,190 --> 00:42:47,150
And I said... I said, "Don't."

513
00:42:48,068 --> 00:42:49,152
Larry looked at me and...

514
00:42:49,236 --> 00:42:51,130
He knew what I was saying.
I knew what I was saying.

515
00:42:51,154 --> 00:42:54,116
That... That poor girl, she fucking knew.

516
00:43:04,668 --> 00:43:06,670
Eventually Larry passed out.

517
00:43:10,924 --> 00:43:14,761
I sat up the rest of the night, in case he woke up with that idea still in his head.

518
00:43:20,017 --> 00:43:24,396
But he just kept sleeping, snoring away.

519
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:29,902
Next morning,
the girl went out with some biker.

520
00:43:33,530 --> 00:43:35,616
You know, I always felt like I fucked up.

521
00:43:37,075 --> 00:43:45,792
I introduced him to, you know,
sex in the wrong way, with the wrong woman. So, I… So maybe that's why he got a taste for killing them?

522
00:43:48,337 --> 00:43:50,881
[Brian] That one thing
didn't make your brother a killer.

523
00:43:50,964 --> 00:43:53,634
- I never said he was a killer.
- [Lauren] But you knew.

524
00:43:53,717 --> 00:43:54,927
I don't. I di-didn't.

525
00:43:55,010 --> 00:43:56,094
You've always known.

526
00:44:00,849 --> 00:44:01,850
[Brian sighs]

527
00:44:09,733 --> 00:44:10,734
Gary.

528
00:44:13,946 --> 00:44:14,947
Gary.

529
00:44:20,202 --> 00:44:39,805
If your brother gets out, and he moves back in here, and he gets his old job back, and life goes back to the way it was… are you gonna be able to stay up every night for the rest of your life to make sure your brother stays where you can see him?

530
00:44:54,361 --> 00:44:56,363
[thunderclap]

531
00:45:20,053 --> 00:45:22,097
[guard] Hey, Jimmy. Come on.

532
00:45:22,181 --> 00:45:25,976
- Come on. Need help here.
- [Jimmy grunts] [guard] Come on. There you go.

533
00:45:28,145 --> 00:45:30,355
- They were supposed to tell me, Jimmy.
- What?

534
00:45:30,439 --> 00:45:33,442
While I was on vacation. If you asked
for me, they were supposed to tell me.

535
00:45:33,525 --> 00:45:34,526
I need a pen.

536
00:45:34,610 --> 00:45:37,738
Okay. Listen, Dr. Hackett's actions
will be subject to review...

537
00:45:37,821 --> 00:45:39,781
- That doesn't matter. I need a pen!
- Okay.

538
00:45:39,865 --> 00:45:42,576
- Jimmy, we're gonna make this right.
- I... I need a pen.

539
00:45:45,954 --> 00:45:47,039
I'll get some paper.

540
00:45:50,542 --> 00:45:51,793
[breathing heavily]

541
00:46:24,535 --> 00:46:27,037
[marker sketching]

542
00:46:53,856 --> 00:46:55,107
What are the dots?

543
00:46:56,900 --> 00:46:57,985
The bodies.

544
00:47:00,112 --> 00:47:01,113
Okay?

545
00:47:02,906 --> 00:47:04,992
They're the bodies. There were 21.

546
00:47:05,075 --> 00:47:06,743
- He had a map.
- Hall had a map?

547
00:47:06,827 --> 00:47:09,830
Of all his dead. I saw it.
This is it, but this is shit.

548
00:47:09,913 --> 00:47:11,123
Okay.

549
00:47:11,206 --> 00:47:12,708
- [crying]
- [Lauren] Jimmy.

550
00:47:16,461 --> 00:47:17,963
We'll work this map, Jimmy.

551
00:47:18,046 --> 00:47:19,047
[crying continues]

552
00:47:19,131 --> 00:47:20,757
We'll see what we can do.

553
00:47:21,341 --> 00:47:22,342
It'll help.

554
00:47:27,472 --> 00:47:28,849
[Lauren sighs]

555
00:47:31,226 --> 00:47:32,477
[Jimmy] He used two belts.

556
00:47:38,942 --> 00:47:39,943
What?

557
00:47:44,156 --> 00:47:45,240
[inhales deeply]

558
00:47:45,866 --> 00:47:49,286
On Jessica Roach. He used two belts
buckled together to strangle her.

559
00:47:55,584 --> 00:47:56,752
He told you that?

560
00:48:00,172 --> 00:48:01,256
In detail.

561
00:48:03,258 --> 00:48:04,343
[exhales sharply]

562
00:48:06,678 --> 00:48:07,846
What else he tell you?

563
00:48:14,019 --> 00:48:17,648
Told me he folded Tricia Reitler's clothes
and placed her earring on top.

564
00:48:25,614 --> 00:48:26,990
Then we got him, Jimmy.

565
00:48:29,034 --> 00:48:30,160
You got him.

566
00:49:04,486 --> 00:49:10,117
Mr. Keene, when last you stood
before this court, you carried an air of entitlement.

567
00:49:11,159 --> 00:49:15,539
You actually wore it like someone would wear their clothes or their skin.

568
00:49:17,040 --> 00:49:18,250
Where'd it go, son?

569
00:49:19,960 --> 00:49:21,211
I don't know, Your Honor.

570
00:49:23,714 --> 00:49:31,889
[judge] Well, judging by the brief
presented to me by Mr. Beaumont, I would venture that you left it behind in that hell that you entered on behalf of this case.

571
00:49:36,268 --> 00:49:40,898
Mr. Keene, the court hereby
commutes your sentence of 120 months for narcotics trafficking.

572
00:49:40,981 --> 00:49:44,902
This commutation is
full without conditions, and effective immediately.

573
00:49:46,153 --> 00:49:47,237
[gavel bangs]

574
00:49:47,779 --> 00:49:49,281
You're a free man, Mr. Keene.

575
00:49:51,658 --> 00:49:52,868
[crying]

576
00:50:01,710 --> 00:50:02,711
Thank you.

577
00:50:14,848 --> 00:50:16,517
I didn't get the bodies for you.

578
00:50:18,894 --> 00:50:20,062
You did plenty.

579
00:50:24,233 --> 00:50:26,360
Hey, Jimmy. I'd like you to meet somebody.

580
00:50:27,945 --> 00:50:29,154
Brian Miller, Jim.

581
00:50:32,115 --> 00:50:33,575
You got the first confession.

582
00:50:34,785 --> 00:50:40,541
You found… Jessica Roach. Yes, I did.

583
00:50:41,458 --> 00:50:42,793
- Jessica.
- [Brian] Yeah.

584
00:50:43,377 --> 00:50:44,378
Yeah.

585
00:50:45,546 --> 00:50:47,714
I just wanted to thank you
for what you did.

586
00:50:52,219 --> 00:50:54,429
Never found out where they're buried.

587
00:50:55,430 --> 00:50:57,391
You made sure he won't bury any more.

588
00:50:58,559 --> 00:50:59,560
Mmm.

589
00:51:08,819 --> 00:51:19,371
[judge 2] The petitioner's claim
that the confessions were coerced, and further, that the petitioner himself had not the mental capacity to understand the charges, does not bear up to scrutiny.

590
00:51:20,956 --> 00:51:35,596
Further, the respondent, working within the boundaries of the existing cases and evidence, has produced further sourcing which confirms the petitioner knew details of the crimes to which he confessed that only the actual perpetrator could know.

591
00:51:36,722 --> 00:51:41,310
It is the decision of this court that the ruling of the criminal court stand.

592
00:51:41,894 --> 00:51:44,313
The petitioner's appeal is hereby denied.

593
00:51:44,813 --> 00:51:49,943
Bailiffs, please remove the prisoner and return him immediately to where he belongs.

594
00:51:50,485 --> 00:51:51,820
Court is adjourned.

595
00:51:51,904 --> 00:51:52,905
[gavel bangs]

596
00:51:53,405 --> 00:51:55,407
[murmuring]

597
00:52:23,769 --> 00:52:24,770
[exhales deeply]

598
00:52:33,487 --> 00:52:34,738
- You see him?
- I see him.

599
00:52:36,198 --> 00:52:37,199
[Big Jim] Ah.

600
00:52:43,539 --> 00:52:44,540
[taxi door closes]

601
00:52:51,046 --> 00:52:52,047
Hey.

602
00:52:53,423 --> 00:52:54,675
[chuckles]

603
00:53:00,681 --> 00:53:02,099
[sighs]

604
00:53:06,103 --> 00:53:07,104
[laughs]

605
00:53:10,440 --> 00:53:11,441
[sobs]

606
00:53:13,527 --> 00:53:14,528
Thank you.

607
00:53:39,511 --> 00:53:41,930
[door closes]

608
00:53:45,350 --> 00:53:46,393
[sniffs]

609
00:54:02,826 --> 00:54:03,827
[grunts]

610
00:54:09,875 --> 00:54:10,876
You okay?

611
00:54:13,003 --> 00:54:14,838
Oh, I can't sleep.

612
00:54:16,381 --> 00:54:19,176
Oh. When I do sleep, it's like I didn't.

613
00:54:19,259 --> 00:54:22,095
It's the apnea, Larry.
They're supposed to be treating that.

614
00:54:25,349 --> 00:54:26,642
What are you gonna do?

615
00:54:27,309 --> 00:54:31,188
You're gonna tell 'em to treat it, Larry.
It was a contributory factor, they said.

616
00:54:32,689 --> 00:54:33,774
Co-Contri...

617
00:54:36,026 --> 00:54:38,362
[stammers] To your suicide try.

618
00:54:39,238 --> 00:54:41,615
What? Wasn't why I did it.

619
00:54:42,950 --> 00:54:44,243
Then why?

620
00:54:50,249 --> 00:54:53,085
- I don't belong in here.
- Yes, you do.

621
00:54:53,168 --> 00:54:55,045
I don't deserve this injus...

622
00:54:56,964 --> 00:54:59,383
"Yes, you do?" What?

623
00:54:59,967 --> 00:55:00,968
You do.

624
00:55:01,468 --> 00:55:04,972
It's all mucked up in your head, man.
It's eating you away.

625
00:55:06,807 --> 00:55:07,850
What?

626
00:55:09,351 --> 00:55:11,562
- The girls, Larry.
- No.

627
00:55:11,645 --> 00:55:13,105
- The girls. Yes.
- No.

628
00:55:13,188 --> 00:55:16,316
You gotta tell people what you did.
You gotta get clear of it.

629
00:55:20,070 --> 00:55:23,824
You're my brother.
You're m... You're my brother.

630
00:55:25,117 --> 00:55:29,246
And I failed you.
I didn't look after you right.

631
00:55:31,039 --> 00:55:35,335
Look, if you... If you get the... the flu,
I'm supposed to get you medicine.

632
00:55:35,878 --> 00:55:39,464
If you're cold, and I have a blanket,
I'm supposed to share it with you.

633
00:55:40,048 --> 00:55:43,677
If you're fucked up in how you think, I'm supposed to help you not do bad things.

634
00:55:43,760 --> 00:55:45,929
[mumbles] No. No, no.

635
00:55:46,471 --> 00:55:49,433
No, Gary. Not... Not you.

636
00:55:52,102 --> 00:55:55,189
I... [stammers, cries]

637
00:55:57,649 --> 00:55:58,859
Look, I, uh...

638
00:56:00,861 --> 00:56:03,322
[sobs]
I need to do what's right here, Larry.

639
00:56:07,618 --> 00:56:08,911
And not for them.

640
00:56:09,453 --> 00:56:11,914
Not for them, but for you.

641
00:56:14,458 --> 00:56:19,630
You're never gonna stop living in fucking… [voice cracks] …agony till you do.

642
00:56:19,713 --> 00:56:21,840
[cries] Gary.

643
00:56:25,802 --> 00:56:27,304
Not you, Gary.

644
00:56:27,387 --> 00:56:31,391
Please. Hey, hey. Please?

645
00:56:33,227 --> 00:56:34,520
Gotta let me help you.

646
00:56:40,192 --> 00:56:41,276
[inhales deeply]

647
00:56:42,569 --> 00:56:48,492
[attendant on PA] Ladies and gentlemen,
our flying time today to Grand Rapids will be approximately 55 minutes.

648
00:56:48,575 --> 00:56:52,871
The captain has turned off
the seat belt sign, so relax and enjoy the flight.

649
00:57:03,048 --> 00:57:04,508
Can I get you anything, sir?

650
00:57:05,884 --> 00:57:07,261
Vodka soda, please.

651
00:57:31,076 --> 00:57:32,077
Lemon or lime?

652
00:57:33,120 --> 00:57:34,121
Lemon.

653
00:57:35,247 --> 00:57:37,875
Huh. Most people choose lime.

654
00:57:41,587 --> 00:57:42,963
I'm a rebel.

655
00:57:44,131 --> 00:57:45,257
A bad boy.

656
00:57:46,842 --> 00:57:48,302
Well, I'm trying to reform.

657
00:57:48,385 --> 00:57:51,346
[laughs] No, you're not.

658
00:57:51,430 --> 00:57:52,472
[chuckles]

659
00:57:53,640 --> 00:57:54,850
What's your name?

660
00:57:54,933 --> 00:57:56,435
Tori. With an "I."

661
00:57:58,187 --> 00:58:00,898
Jimmy. With a "Y."

662
00:58:01,565 --> 00:58:03,984
[chuckles] Nice to meet you, Jimmy.

663
00:58:04,860 --> 00:58:06,612
Nice to meet you, Tori with an "I".

664
00:58:15,329 --> 00:58:17,331
["Lucky Man" playing]
